1
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:13,567
Never secured a medical license?

2
00:00:13,633 --> 00:00:15,600
I'm not sure if what
I think is right.

3
00:00:15,667 --> 00:00:17,967
Do you really have a doctor's
license, Mommy?

4
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:18,967
Of course!

5
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:20,800
Did someone tell you about it?

6
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:23,500
You are fired.

7
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:25,567
Please. Can we talk about this?

8
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:27,967
I'm sorry if you won't like
what I'm going to say.

9
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:30,700
The way you discipline her
is wrong.

10
00:00:30,767 --> 00:00:33,267
Don't you dare lecture me
as if you know better.

11
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,867
You didn't raise any child.

12
00:00:34,967 --> 00:00:36,567
How are my children?

13
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:38,567
Your children are not with me.

14
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:40,900
I'm so glad that you can now
walk little by little.

15
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:44,800
Don't you think what the article
says is true?

16
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:47,500
That mommy is not a real doctor.

17
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:50,533
I just want to see them.

18
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,967
I won't talk to them.

19
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,967
They didn't grow up with me.

20
00:00:54,033 --> 00:00:55,300
You're doing it, Mookie.

21
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:31,233
You can do it.

22
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,967
You're doing it, Mookie.

23
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:45,100
There.

24
00:01:47,267 --> 00:01:50,800
Didn't you tell Virgie that
you wanted to have a child?

25
00:01:50,867 --> 00:01:51,700
You were going to adopt

26
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:53,200
because you couldn't
bear a child.

27
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:57,200
Yes, but I had a problem.

28
00:01:57,900 --> 00:02:00,533
I couldn't take care of them.

29
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:04,567
I wanted to find you
so I could return the children.

30
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:07,600
But my friend told me

31
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:11,700
that she knew someone
who wanted to adopt.

32
00:02:11,767 --> 00:02:14,033
That's where they
brought the children.

33
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:18,633
So I don't know where they are
or who adopted them.

34
00:02:18,733 --> 00:02:19,900
I don't know anything.

35
00:02:24,767 --> 00:02:26,933
Where's your friend?

36
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:32,133
My friend passed away.

37
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:37,567
So, I really don't know
where your children are.

38
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:38,867
I really don't know.

39
00:02:54,067 --> 00:02:54,767
Olive!

40
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:56,133
Let me go, Astrid!

41
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,067
I'm not done yet
with Emma and Mookie!

42
00:02:58,133 --> 00:02:59,167
I'll get even with them!

43
00:02:59,233 --> 00:03:00,300
Olive!

44
00:03:00,367 --> 00:03:01,567
That's enough!

45
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:02,533
I knew it!

46
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:06,333
Emma is a traitor.

47
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:08,533
I should've never allowed
that scheming Emma

48
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,467
to enter my house!

49
00:03:10,533 --> 00:03:12,867
Mookie has learned
to lie to me.

50
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,900
Astrid, they're
ganging up on me.

51
00:03:15,967 --> 00:03:20,133
Olive, you can't think straight
if you don't calm down.

52
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:24,200
You know I hate being
betrayed, right?

53
00:03:25,067 --> 00:03:27,533
Olive, leave them be.

54
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,867
Did you come here to
stop me with my plans?

55
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:39,600
In the first place,
why am I even talking to you?

56
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:41,400
Didn't I fire you?

57
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:43,800
Didn't I kick you
out of my life?

58
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:45,333
Then leave me alone

59
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:48,367
and let me deal
with my own business.

60
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:49,767
No, Olive!

61
00:03:50,733 --> 00:03:52,967
I won't repeat
what I did before.

62
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,333
I said leave.

63
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,767
Olive, you're right.

64
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:01,467
I won't survive without you.

65
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:04,433
I was so dumb that
I went against you.

66
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:07,400
Whatever your plans are,
whatever you want to do,

67
00:04:07,467 --> 00:04:09,000
I will stay out of it.

68
00:04:09,767 --> 00:04:11,033
Just please forgive me.

69
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:19,767
Even if those plans...

70
00:04:20,933 --> 00:04:23,733
include Emma and Mookie in it?

71
00:04:36,467 --> 00:04:38,433
Olive Caparas.

72
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:41,300
Artemis Pharmacy owner.

73
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:42,967
About Olive Caparas.

74
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:46,767
Meet Olive Caparas,
the owner of Artemis Pharmacy,

75
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:49,500
a well-known health
establishment.

76
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:50,833
With her leadership,

77
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:52,600
the pharmacy has become
a trusted name

78
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,800
in providing healthcare
solution.

79
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:57,033
What's your plan?

80
00:04:57,100 --> 00:05:00,367
Why are you so interested
in Olive Caparas?

81
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:02,833
I want to know something
about her,

82
00:05:02,933 --> 00:05:04,333
so let's search for more.

83
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:06,900
We might see something else.

84
00:05:06,967 --> 00:05:10,567
Didn't I tell you to
leave Madam alone?

85
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:13,967
Mother, I just want
to help Mookie.

86
00:05:14,033 --> 00:05:16,167
You care about nothing
but Mookie!

87
00:05:16,233 --> 00:05:17,267
Hey!

88
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:17,733
- Hey!
- Mother!
Hey!

89
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:19,600
Stop it, Ligaya.

90
00:05:20,667 --> 00:05:21,633
That's my laptop.

91
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,800
Let it go! That's mine!

92
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:25,600
You did nothing but interfere
with Mookie's life!

93
00:05:25,667 --> 00:05:27,033
I hear about nothing but Mookie!

94
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,100
Son of a gun!

95
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:33,133
My child uses this
in his online class!

96
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,600
This isn't fully paid yet!

97
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:36,667
You almost destroyed it!

98
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:38,367
What did we do wrong?

99
00:05:38,433 --> 00:05:40,533
Emma is so annoying!

100
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,967
She does nothing but interfere
in someone else's life!

101
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:45,567
What's your problem, Mother?

102
00:05:45,633 --> 00:05:48,833
Why do you always see
what I do with Mookie?

103
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,867
She has her mother!

104
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:53,333
Whatever her mother wants
to do with her

105
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,867
is none of your business!

106
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:57,200
Because you're not the mother!

107
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:58,733
Madam is!

108
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,900
Stop thinking that
you're still a mother.

109
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:02,433
Because your daughter
has long been gone!

110
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,400
You're way out of line, Mother!

111
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:07,700
You don't care even if
Ma'am Olive hurts Mookie

112
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,067
because that's how you are!

113
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:11,167
Are you blaming me again?

114
00:06:11,233 --> 00:06:11,933
Me?

115
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,467
Isn't it true?

116
00:06:14,467 --> 00:06:19,667
You came to my graduation drunk.

117
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:21,367
You made me a laughingstock.

118
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:22,267
Shut up.

119
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:26,967
I worked as a dishwasher

120
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:28,667
when I was nine to bring home
even a porridge.

121
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:30,533
- Because we had nothing to eat!
- I said stop!

122
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:34,833
I taught myself to be brave
at a very young age.

123
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,200
Because you were always
not there for me.

124
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:40,633
I couldn't rely on you because
you're a worthless mother!

125
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,967
You're heartless!

126
00:06:42,067 --> 00:06:43,767
If I'm heartless,

127
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:47,933
I won't get hurt like this
for not finding your siblings!

128
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:06,767
What did you say, Mother?

129
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:07,967
Siblings?

130
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:10,133
I have siblings?

131
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:11,967
Oh, dear.

132
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:14,833
Mother.

133
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:17,367
Mother, answer me.
Do I have siblings?

134
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:19,400
Mother, where are they?

135
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:25,267
They're gone.

136
00:07:26,433 --> 00:07:27,900
I gave them away.

137
00:07:29,467 --> 00:07:30,700
You gave them in exchange
for what?

138
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:32,633
Money?

139
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:34,833
For alcohol?

140
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:35,633
No.

141
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:36,867
- Money for gambling?
- No!

142
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:41,700
The other one was sick.

143
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:43,133
I couldn't bring her
to the hospital.

144
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,833
I had no means.

145
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:47,400
It's because you didn't
want to make sacrifices, right?

146
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:50,767
You didn't want to make
sacrifices for your children!

147
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:53,667
That's why you also wanted me to
give Baby Kayla up for adoption!

148
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:55,467
No, it's not like that!

149
00:07:55,533 --> 00:07:56,900
You don't understand.

150
00:07:56,967 --> 00:07:58,800
It's so clear, Mother!

151
00:07:58,867 --> 00:08:00,400
You don't love them!

152
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:04,100
You wouldn't give up on them
if you loved them!

153
00:08:04,167 --> 00:08:05,167
- You should've fought for them!
- No.

154
00:08:05,233 --> 00:08:06,133
Stop.
Because that's how
a mother should be.

155
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:09,667
- You should've protected them!
- Stop!

156
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:10,833
Stop!

157
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:13,000
Did you know what I told myself

158
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:15,700
whenever I got hurt
when I was a kid?

159
00:08:15,767 --> 00:08:20,133
I wish I had a sibling
who could help me.

160
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,600
Turns out I have siblings.

161
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:26,233
But you gave them away
like trash.

162
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:30,367
You know, you're no better
than Ma'am Olive.

163
00:08:30,433 --> 00:08:32,500
You're a worthless mother!

164
00:08:40,667 --> 00:08:41,467
Ligaya.

165
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:42,767
Ligaya!

166
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,300
Ligaya!

167
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:00,933
Are you okay now?

168
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:08,100
Did you see Emma
and Mookie earlier?

169
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:13,300
They seem very, very close.

170
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:19,533
I haven't seen Mookie
smile like that

171
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,300
whenever she's with me.

172
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,633
Maybe Emma is good with kids.

173
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,867
And you know why?

174
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:36,367
Because she lost a child.

175
00:09:39,067 --> 00:09:40,267
That's why...

176
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:46,133
she's slowly turning my daughter
against me.

177
00:09:48,033 --> 00:09:50,733
She wants to take my daughter
away from me.

178
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:54,767
Olive, you're just overthinking.

179
00:09:56,567 --> 00:09:57,367
No.

180
00:10:00,067 --> 00:10:02,933
The night I heard
a phone ringing...

181
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,533
I knew it was Emma.

182
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:11,000
They're both in
the storage room.

183
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,000
They're betraying me.

184
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:25,233
She's been telling Mookie
all sorts of lies.

185
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:29,767
She's poisoning my
daughter's mind,

186
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,400
so that she will hate me.

187
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:35,933
She's doing that to
get Mookie's trust.

188
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:38,200
So she can take my
daughter away from me.

189
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:44,100
Olive, please don't jump
into any conclusion.

190
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:51,467
I'm glad you stopped me earlier.

191
00:10:53,633 --> 00:10:59,100
Because it's not enough
to just fire and hurt Emma.

192
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:03,233
What do you mean?

193
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:08,600
She needs to understand the
consequence...

194
00:11:10,533 --> 00:11:12,333
of betraying me.

195
00:11:25,167 --> 00:11:29,400
Wow, I just stepped out earlier,

196
00:11:29,467 --> 00:11:32,733
and Ligaya already stirred up
drama in the afternoon prime.

197
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:35,400
Come on, Wiro.

198
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:37,567
Maybe you should stop for now.

199
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:40,500
You can already see that
Ligaya is troubled.

200
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:43,333
Can you blame me?

201
00:11:45,667 --> 00:11:47,067
I had nothing back then.

202
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:49,400
I was having a hard time.

203
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:52,367
I couldn't get a job.

204
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:57,133
Should I just wait
for my child to die

205
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,700
because I had no money
to buy medicine?

206
00:11:58,767 --> 00:11:59,900
Is that it?

207
00:12:10,433 --> 00:12:11,333
Hey, hey.
Wait, wait.

208
00:12:12,133 --> 00:12:13,800
You've had enough.

209
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:15,700
You're already drunk.

210
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:21,767
My heart was being crushed
whenever I saw my children sick.

211
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,900
Which mother's heart
wouldn't be shattered?

212
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:34,333
Emma doesn't know
what I went through.

213
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,400
That's why she won't understand.

214
00:12:37,967 --> 00:12:40,867
I did that because I only
wanted what was best

215
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:42,200
for my children.

216
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:44,533
Is that bad?

217
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:47,133
Kutsy?

218
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,000
Wiro?

219
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:49,133
Is that bad?

220
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:52,200
Answer me!

221
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:53,567
- I look like a fool here.
- No!

222
00:12:53,633 --> 00:12:54,433
I'm talking to you.
It's just the three of us.

223
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,067
No, no, no.

224
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:57,200
- Here it is.
- Okay, okay.

225
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:58,833
- Here it is.
- Okay, okay.

226
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:00,233
Okay, let's drink some more.

227
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:02,667
Come on. Yes, let's drink.

228
00:13:02,733 --> 00:13:03,733
We're not going to stop.

229
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,367
We're going to get wasted.

230
00:13:05,433 --> 00:13:09,400
- We'll drink 'til sunrise.
- We will go home crawling.

231
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:11,167
- Let's get wasted.
- Come on, drink.

232
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:13,300
Here's your shot.

233
00:13:13,367 --> 00:13:15,367
Bottom's up.

234
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,833
Here you go, Emma.

235
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:30,300
I still can't understand why...

236
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:35,700
mother gave my siblings away.

237
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:44,567
Maybe she has a reason
to do that.

238
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,033
I don't understand, Dan.

239
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:54,867
Mother has children.

240
00:13:54,967 --> 00:13:56,300
But she gave them away.

241
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,400
Ma'am Olive...

242
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:02,000
also has a child.

243
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:04,000
But she's torturing the kid.

244
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,967
They're so lucky.

245
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,733
Why is it that I...

246
00:14:11,933 --> 00:14:15,967
who wanted to have children
and care for them...

247
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,600
is being deprived of that?

248
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:23,900
Emma, you're different
from them.

249
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,867
You're different.

250
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:42,233
I have your necklace repaired.

251
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,133
Next time,

252
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,233
make sure you take care
of everything I give you.

253
00:14:48,933 --> 00:14:50,867
That's very expensive.

254
00:14:53,467 --> 00:14:54,800
Yes, Mommy.

255
00:14:58,233 --> 00:15:01,400
Mommy, what are those
medications for?

256
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:05,000
Will that make my legs better?

257
00:15:05,067 --> 00:15:05,633
No.

258
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:09,800
Ouch.

259
00:15:14,567 --> 00:15:16,033
Ouch, Mommy.

260
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:18,967
This one...

261
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:25,633
I will just test if you're
allergic to this medication.

262
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,667
New meds again, Mommy?

263
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:36,000
I have a feeling that you're
hiding something from me.

264
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:38,400
Hold still.

265
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:41,400
I need to find your vein.

266
00:15:45,467 --> 00:15:47,167
Did you know that...

267
00:15:48,867 --> 00:15:55,767
lying, for me,
is like a serious illness.

268
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,100
It's like cancer.

269
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:08,367
So, the next time
you lie to me,

270
00:16:09,167 --> 00:16:10,667
there will be a consequence.

271
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,800
New medication.

272
00:16:51,133 --> 00:16:53,867
Mother, I admit.

273
00:16:53,933 --> 00:16:56,233
I'm upset with you.

274
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:59,967
But I think Danilo is right.

275
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:06,167
Maybe you have a serious reason
why you gave my siblings away.

276
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:10,700
But why, Mother?

277
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:15,600
How could you be away from them?

278
00:17:28,733 --> 00:17:30,833
I was still pregnant with you...

279
00:17:32,633 --> 00:17:34,367
when your father died.

280
00:17:39,033 --> 00:17:42,733
I didn't know how I could
raise your siblings.

281
00:17:43,567 --> 00:17:44,733
For a mother,

282
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:50,400
there's nothing more painful
than seeing her children suffer.

283
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:55,433
Dear, don't close your eyes.

284
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,300
My child has a
chronic lung disease?

285
00:18:01,367 --> 00:18:02,433
Yes, Ma'am.

286
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:06,800
It's called bronchopulmonary
dysplasia or BPD.

287
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:09,000
The child can survive for now.

288
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:11,900
But the symptoms will recur,

289
00:18:11,967 --> 00:18:16,067
and her life can be in danger
if she isn't treated fully.

290
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:19,067
My god.

291
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,433
My god.

292
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:26,433
I don't have the money to pay
for my child's treatment.

293
00:18:28,167 --> 00:18:29,700
Doc, what do I do?

294
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:32,867
I don't want to lose her.

295
00:18:32,933 --> 00:18:34,833
I want to save my child, Doc.

296
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:44,267
Ma'am Alice wanted to adopt
both of your siblings.

297
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:50,867
I didn't think it through.

298
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:57,300
All I wanted was for your
sibling to get better.

299
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:02,700
Do you know where they are now?

300
00:19:09,533 --> 00:19:11,500
I tried to find them.

301
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,567
I did my best.

302
00:19:14,867 --> 00:19:19,733
But I still don't know
where they are.

303
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:25,967
I'll understand
if you'll get mad at me.

304
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:30,700
I only thought about
your sibling's welfare.

305
00:19:32,733 --> 00:19:34,300
Please forgive me, Emma.

306
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:42,933
Forgive me.

307
00:19:55,733 --> 00:19:56,567
What's this?

308
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:00,200
Is this my last meal?

309
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,867
Mother, don't be like that.

310
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,300
I know.

311
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,167
You also see me as a bad person.

312
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:19,100
Emma told me why
you gave them away.

313
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,000
I understand you, Mother.

314
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:28,000
Are you just pretending
to be nice?

315
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:33,233
You don't know how
to be a mother.

316
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:35,333
You won't understand me.

317
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:53,567
Ma'am, you wanted to see me?

318
00:20:55,267 --> 00:20:57,933
Have you seen a snake, Emma?

319
00:20:58,567 --> 00:20:59,200
Ma'am?

320
00:21:03,133 --> 00:21:05,133
Have you seen a snake?

321
00:21:07,133 --> 00:21:07,867
Yes.

322
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:15,933
Does it look like you?

323
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:26,000
Oh, come on, Emma.

324
00:21:26,967 --> 00:21:28,100
I'm just kidding.

325
00:21:28,767 --> 00:21:30,533
Where's your sense of humor?

326
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:32,667
Don't worry.

327
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:36,200
You don't look like any snake.

328
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:41,633
Because you outshined them all.

329
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:48,267
You are the most beautiful
and the best of them all.

330
00:21:58,700 --> 00:21:59,567
Ma'am...

331
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,000
can I go home now?

332
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:05,900
I'm done with the laundry.

333
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,733
Actually, Emma...

334
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:15,133
I have a special task for you.

335
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:22,200
I noticed that the storage room
is dirty.

336
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:27,267
So, if it's okay with you,
can you clean it?

337
00:22:28,967 --> 00:22:30,100
Maybe there's already...

338
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:35,733
an unwelcome guest, a snake,
living there...

339
00:22:36,967 --> 00:22:39,000
without my knowledge.

340
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,200
Mommy?

341
00:23:09,167 --> 00:23:10,100
Why?

342
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:11,900
Nothing.

343
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:41,167
Where's my necklace?

344
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:45,933
Hello, Astrid?

345
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:49,200
Are you ready to make it up
to me?

346
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:52,633
Good.

347
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:56,067
Then, you know what to do.

348
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,467
What's this?

349
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:54,500
How did this get here?

350
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:01,067
Ma'am Astrid, what are you
doing here?

351
00:25:01,133 --> 00:25:03,067
Why are you with the police?

352
00:25:03,167 --> 00:25:05,033
- Let's go, Mister. Hurry.
- Wait, Mister.

353
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:05,667
- Ma'am.
- Let's go inside.
Wait, Ma'am.

354
00:25:06,633 --> 00:25:07,733
Does Ma'am Olive know
about this?

355
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:09,000
Ma'am!

356
00:25:14,033 --> 00:25:15,933
I knew it.

357
00:25:16,933 --> 00:25:18,600
You're stealing from us.

358
00:25:19,533 --> 00:25:20,567
No, Ma'am.

359
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:24,100
Arrest that woman, Sir.

360
00:25:24,633 --> 00:25:26,133
She's the woman who broke
into our house the other night.

361
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:29,400
And now, she's caught red-handed
stealing from us again!

362
00:25:42,267 --> 00:25:45,800
How could you steal from me
after giving you a job?

363
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:48,033
You turned my house
into a grocery store.

364
00:25:48,100 --> 00:25:49,467
You planted all of that.

365
00:25:49,533 --> 00:25:51,267
Even the necklace in the room.

366
00:25:51,333 --> 00:25:53,467
She's crazy.

367
00:25:53,533 --> 00:25:58,000
If only I could give a statement
to the police, I would.

368
00:25:58,067 --> 00:26:04,000
I would tell them that
Mommy Emma is innocent.

369
00:26:04,067 --> 00:26:05,133
I have an idea.

370
00:26:06,133 --> 00:26:07,833
Maybe I can help you.

371
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:10,767
Make sure you can file
the case within 24 hours.

372
00:26:11,333 --> 00:26:13,500
Spare no cost in
expediting it.

373
00:26:13,567 --> 00:26:15,467
We will fight Olive.

374
00:26:15,533 --> 00:26:16,467
How?
She has plenty of money
to pay a lawyer.

375
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:18,800
She's influential.

376
00:26:18,867 --> 00:26:20,133
She has so many connections.

377
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:22,300
How can we win over her?

378
00:26:22,367 --> 00:26:28,433
Emma isn't that kind of person,
unless she was framed up.
